r service</span><hr size=1> it probably depends what your petitioning for, if your stuck and stuff like that you'll probably get response faster...If you tell them &quot;arrgh all my implants disappeared in the tir crash&quot; you just have to wait I guess. They're kinda fast to respond to general criticism ,like : &quot;this game sucks, I cant move wtf are you doing, aaah&quot;, then they always answer =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uskipsanders.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SkipSanders</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.san.rr.com/skip/Tiran.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiny Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#660000>(10/14/01 12:52:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.san.rr.com/skip/Tiran.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A new low in customer service</span><hr size=1> True, TeffaMA.  If you petition a 'bug', they'll mostly ignore it, because bugs aren't to be reported by petition.<br><br>If you're 'stuck', they'll usually respond.  Reporting exploiters probably gets faster response, too, though they might not TELL you they've come to watch invisibly.<br><br>Not that I've needed to petition anything since beta, but I do expect there is a petition 'triage' going on, given all the people who've said they're reporting bugs, even though they've been told not to do that, so the queue is overloaded. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uteffama.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TeffaMA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#660000>(10/14/01 1:31:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A new low in customer service</span><hr size=1> theres zero use of petitioning a bug anyway, the anwser you'll get is : send a feedback,bugreport.<br>One ark even told me it was no more use talking to him about it then talking to any other player. So theres no way at all to get in contact with funcom except the bugreports and maybe their board ,allthou they'll delete any thread that dosent include lines like &quot;funcom roxxors, great game&quot;etc... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=publius>Publius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#660000>(10/14/01 2:02:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A new low in customer service</span><hr size=1> I have to disagree.<br><br>First, this particular petition was not about a bug. I have never petitioned to complain about a bug. On the occasions when I have sent petitions, it was always because I had a very real problem that I needed help with.<br><br>About 5 weeks ago, I was stuck inside a building. Not that I was in a shop, but I was inside a solid brush, because the door had failed on the way in. I sent petitions explaining that I was STUCK, and waited over an hour. During that hour, three other people got stuck in there with me the same way. Nobody ever answered my petitions, not then or even later, to follow up.<br><br>ARK's suck the big mtondo, and Funcom does too. There <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> is</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> no Customer Support, whatever the fanboys may say. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uyuzhanvong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yuzhan Vong</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://image.fg-a.com/Usfla2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiny Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#660000>(10/14/01 7:18:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ebicom.net/~bookster/vonghead.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A new low in customer service</span><hr size=1> the reason you didnt get a response was probably because all of the idiots petitioning bugs, and all that other crap. I think they should ban/suspend people who petition crap more than once. Use the 3strikes rule: <br>First time you petition a bug/crap tell them,&quot;Look dont petition that here is what you are supposed to do.&quot; <br>Second time, &quot;This is a warning do not petition this kind of stuff again&quot;. <br>Third time, &quot;You are now suspended for a week&quot; <br> <p><IMG SRC="http://www.cableone.net/alton/usa.gif"BORDER=0><font face="Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, san-serif" color="#800040">I fear that all we have done is awakened a sleeping giant, and filled it with a desire for vengeance. -- Adm. Yamamoto, after the attack on Pearl Harbor</font> <br><IMG src="http://www.ebicom.net/~alton/sig1.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uteffama.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TeffaMA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#660000>(10/14/01 8:31:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A new low in customer service</span><hr size=1> I usually get my &quot;sdfsdffjk&quot; petitions responded =P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/usepulus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sepulus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Martial, Baby, MARTIAL.</span><br>  Posts: 447<br> <font color=#660000>(10/15/01 1:32:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A new low in customer service</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;the reason you didnt get a response was probably because all of the idiots petitioning bugs, and all that other crap.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>Does it really matter why your petitions arent being answered?  No.<br><br>There is a very easy way around this, hire for fucking GM's.  We wouldnt have this problem if they hired 40+ more GM's.  Stop relying on ARKs and do your own job.  Customer service isnt customer service if they cant get to you no matter the reason.<br><br>I have a feeling that people wouldnt be leaving as fast as they are if they had better logs and much more GM's <p>- Sepulus</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=publius>Publius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#660000>(10/15/01 4:19:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A new low in customer service</span><hr size=1> To give the 'Com their fair due, they did eventually answer and fix my problem. It took them 46 hours, almost to the exact minute. In that time I sent roughly 15-18 petitions. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/umingz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mingz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 168<br> <font color=#660000>(10/15/01 5:52:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A new low in customer service</span><hr size=1> One great thing about being an MA (well opi MA in particular) is that our agility allows us to jump REALLY freakin' high. As a lowbie there were several occasions where I was stuck in the geometry. I petitioned, but never got any help and always just /term'd. <br><br>At 230+ agility, however I've found that within dungeons anyway, I can jump through the ceiling and this can be handy. When the client lags...often you'll move forward and regain control in area's you didn't intend to be. The worse of these times is when you end up in a place where you cannot go, like in the rooms with the the triple sliding doors and the tank full of bubbling liquid. When the client lags...the game doesn't check for geometry collisions and will put you in these places. Ever been on a catwalk bridge, lag and end up under it?  Anyway..if you get stuck in these places...try logging. If however that fails, find any piece of geometry. Shelves..nooks, boxes, whatever and jump onto them. Anything that is solid will support you regardless of size. Then jump through the upper Z axis geometry. You'll end up on top of the overall floorplan in the void (hehe daggerfall memories) and from there you need only walk until you fall back through in the regulation area.<br><br>  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=publius>Publius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#660000>(10/15/01 7:20:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wild applause for Mingz!</span><hr size=1> Oh yeah, dude!<br><br>That is arguably one of the very best and most useful tips I have ever seen posted here <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uruney3.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Runey3</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#660000>(10/16/01 8:07:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.runeyandbunbun.com/images/color/thumbsdself3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wild applause for Mingz!</span><hr size=1> Hahaha the return of Void-walking~! I miss that from DF. Well, not miss it, exactly, but...it made quests so much easier to step outside the dungeon walls and float to where you needed to go. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=illith>ILLITH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#660000>(11/2/01 3:34:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wild applause for Mingz!</span><hr size=1> i thought jump hight was dependent on runspeed oh well. i have fun jumping over these really larg atrox enforces.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=39.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.showNextMessage?topicID=39.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=12><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.emailToFriend?topicID=39.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.threadControl?topicID=39.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)<